description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthiastic and experienced Nurse to join Catch22; a service who focus on helping young people up to the age of 25 with substance misuse issues. In this role you would be bringingyour mental health expertise to not only support the young people butalso the team. Using your leadership skills and expertise you will work witht the leadership team to develop those your work with and develop the network with mental health services within Surrey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You willmanage a defined caseload ofyoung peoplewithmental health and substance misuse needs. In this role you will facilitate the promotion and maintenance of a high standard of communitymental healthcare involving assessment of needs, planning, implementation of treatment/care plans and the evaluation of programmes of care and risk assessment/management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the leadership team you may need to provide supervision and teaching programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surrey and Borders Partnership NHS Foundation Trust (SABP) will be your employing body and you will be seconded to Catch22. Clinical supervision will be provided by the Nurse Consultant within the Childrens and Young Peoples Division at SABP. The Nurse Consultant will jointly provide yearly appraisals with the Service Manager at Catch22. There will be an opportunity to work closely with our Adult Substance Misuse Service Iaccess wihin this role. Ideally you will have experience of substance misuse work and/or adult mental health/CAMHS community experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are various opportunities for growth and development and we would look to provide an individualistic approach to cater for your learning needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
